10:35.426 --> 10:37.883
I'm serious!
Look, I got a sick mama.

10:37.929 --> 10:40.636
(laughs) A sick mama.
Wow, original.

10:40.682 --> 10:44.174
Wow. You have a hard time
trusting people, don't you?

10:45.019 --> 10:46.008
No.

10:47.021 --> 10:48.056
You know...

10:48.898 --> 10:50.354
you look really trustworthy,

10:50.400 --> 10:52.482
so l'm-a tell you the truth.

10:54.154 --> 10:56.315
I got a lot of people relying on me.

10:57.031 --> 10:58.020
Oh, yeah?

10:59.033 --> 11:01.240
Yeah! A lot of people.

11:01.995 --> 11:05.078
Look, I'm like their personal ATM, okay?

11:05.123 --> 11:07.034
- (laughs) Shut up.
- Don't laugh. It ain't funny. I'm serious.

11:07.083 --> 11:10.371
Officer, look. It's not easy
trying to be the hero.

11:10.420 --> 11:11.580
- Oh.
- It really isn't.

11:11.629 --> 11:13.620
(Luke) They're ready for us.

11:16.634 --> 11:18.295
Don't look so scared, Benny.

11:18.344 --> 11:21.131
Officer McNally will hold your hand.

11:22.140 --> 11:24.597
The object measures
just under a centimeter.

11:24.642 --> 11:26.803
Right, width of a 9-millimeter bullet.

11:26.853 --> 11:29.060
It entered here,
partially penetrated the skull,

11:29.105 --> 11:31.061
embedded itself in the frontal lobe.
It's--

11:31.107 --> 11:32.972
Oh, hold on.
It's in my brain?

11:33.026 --> 11:35.358
(sighs) If you're going
to get shot in the head,

11:35.403 --> 11:36.768
the frontal lobe's the best spot.

11:36.821 --> 11:40.279
And, uh, it also was slowed down by--

11:40.325 --> 11:42.441
I understand it passed through another victim?

11:42.493 --> 11:44.074
- Exactly.
- No way.

11:44.120 --> 11:47.032
I wasn't there, all right.
I live in a rough neighborhood.

11:47.081 --> 11:48.332
It was a stray bullet.

11:48.374 --> 11:49.625
Are you in any pain?

11:49.667 --> 11:51.999
A lot of pain.
I think I need painkillers.

11:52.045 --> 11:53.034
(scoffs)

11:53.087 --> 11:55.544
Look, um... can...

11:55.590 --> 11:56.670
can you remove it?

11:56.716 --> 11:58.957
Hey, hey. Whoa, whoa.
You asked for an X-ray.

11:59.010 --> 11:59.999
- Listen, just--
- Yeah.

12:00.053 --> 12:03.671
The fact is that people can survive years
with shrapnel lodged in their bodies.

12:03.723 --> 12:05.714
So |'||--|'|| be okay.

12:05.767 --> 12:07.473
I can live with it, right?

12:07.518 --> 12:09.474
My concern here is the bullet.

12:09.520 --> 12:11.647
I need this to put a murderer in jail.

12:11.689 --> 12:14.101
And I need the patient's consent
in order to proceed.

12:14.150 --> 12:15.230
Yeah. And I don't give it.

12:15.276 --> 12:17.517
Fine. I'll get a search warrant.

12:19.155 --> 12:20.315
McNally.

12:24.452 --> 12:26.568
You stay here.
Keep an eye on our man Benny.

12:26.621 --> 12:28.031
I'm gonna talk to the prosecutor.

12:28.081 --> 12:29.867
There's a surgeon on shift
who's willing to operate.

12:29.916 --> 12:32.999
Okay, but we're sure that,
you know, he's involved?

12:33.044 --> 12:34.329
Like, he's notjust a witness?

12:34.379 --> 12:35.960
There's a bullet inside
his head that killed a man

12:36.005 --> 12:37.745
that we all know
came from Kraker's gun.

12:37.799 --> 12:39.505
I need that bullet.

12:39.550 --> 12:41.006
Okay, what do I do
if he tries to leave?

12:41.052 --> 12:44.340
(sighs) Keep him talking.
Gain his trust.

12:44.389 --> 12:46.505
If anyone can do it, it's you.

12:46.557 --> 12:48.138
Who knows? Maybe you can
convince him to do it.

12:55.400 --> 12:56.389
I'll check on you later.

12:58.236 --> 13:00.022
Those pills should knock him out
for a couple hours.

13:00.071 --> 13:01.060
- I'll be back.
- Okay.

13:03.574 --> 13:05.405
(sighs) You doing okay?

13:05.451 --> 13:08.238
Oh... (sighs)
I don't like hospitals.

13:08.997 --> 13:10.362
I think I like sedatives, though.

13:13.251 --> 13:15.458
Benny, can we please
talk about last week?

13:16.754 --> 13:18.210
Last week?

13:18.256 --> 13:19.462
The parking garage.

13:19.507 --> 13:21.168
I know you saw Kraker shoot that man.

13:21.217 --> 13:24.175
You know, itjust would--
it would really help me out

13:24.220 --> 13:26.051
if you could tell me
exactly what happened.

13:30.643 --> 13:32.634
(snoring)

13:33.271 --> 13:34.681
Or not.

13:36.566 --> 13:38.022
(sighs)

13:38.067 --> 13:40.023
Gail, your seat belt.

13:40.069 --> 13:43.106
Crap.

13:43.156 --> 13:45.067
Wait. What are you doing?

13:45.116 --> 13:47.778
I got blood on my shirt.

13:48.911 --> 13:49.900
(police radio chatter)

13:49.954 --> 13:52.286
- Can you stop staring?
- I'm not staring.

13:54.167 --> 13:56.123
So what did the old geezer
have to say for himself?

13:58.212 --> 14:00.168
He's, like, a retired schoolteacher.

14:00.214 --> 14:01.294
He's--He's, like, 80.

14:01.341 --> 14:03.957
He shouldn't have been on the road.

14:04.010 --> 14:06.592
You know the guy that he killed?
He has, like, kids.

14:06.637 --> 14:07.888
Poor guy was on the way to work.

14:09.849 --> 14:13.512
You know, the driver was probably on, like,
a senior's cocktail. I've seen that before.

14:14.312 --> 14:15.973
Senior's cocktail?

14:16.022 --> 14:17.978
Yeah, my grandmother was on it.

14:18.024 --> 14:21.312
She was on, like, ten different
kinds of medication,

14:21.361 --> 14:24.273
and she just acted like
a crazy bat out of hell

14:24.322 --> 14:25.437
at the slightest provocation.

14:25.490 --> 14:26.980
He didn't seem crazy.

14:27.033 --> 14:30.446
ln shock, maybe.
But he called me a good boy.

14:30.495 --> 14:33.453
- That's really creepy.
- Right?

14:33.498 --> 14:35.159
Probably high as a kite.

14:35.208 --> 14:37.119
You know, I probably should've
asked him about that--

14:37.168 --> 14:39.409
like, if he was on any type
of medication or anything.

14:39.462 --> 14:41.043
Yeah, Chris, you probably
should've asked him that.

14:42.173 --> 14:43.504
You gonna put your belt on?

14:47.011 --> 14:49.172
Putting my seat belt on, okay?
I'm buckling up.

14:49.222 --> 14:50.758
(seat belt clicks)
You happy?

15:03.528 --> 15:05.018
(sighs)

15:10.910 --> 15:12.025
Excuse me.

15:12.537 --> 15:13.993
Where's the guy in 402?

15:14.038 --> 15:16.529
He woke up, had to go to the can.

15:21.462 --> 15:22.497
Hey.

15:40.398 --> 15:42.354
(big band ringtone blaring)

15:42.400 --> 15:45.187
Sammy, you gotta change that ringer, man.
It's deadly.

15:45.236 --> 15:46.976
Yeah. (turns off ringtone)

15:47.947 --> 15:48.936
What?

15:48.990 --> 15:50.230
(Andy) I need your help.

15:50.283 --> 15:52.194
I thought you were with Callaghan.

15:52.243 --> 15:54.950
Yeah, well, he left me in charge
of guarding some evidence.

15:54.996 --> 15:56.611
Well, it's a witness, actually.

15:56.664 --> 15:58.404
It's a witness with some evidence.

15:58.458 --> 16:00.198
McNally, I already have a headache.

16:00.251 --> 16:02.207
Look, I lost the witness, okay?

16:02.253 --> 16:04.209
The doctor said he was
gonna be asleep for hours.

16:04.255 --> 16:06.541
The doctor said?
The doctor is not a cop.

16:06.591 --> 16:07.580
Where's Callaghan?

16:07.633 --> 16:10.625
Okay, listen, I gotta find this kid
before Luke finds out that I lost him.

16:10.678 --> 16:12.464
And I care because, uh...

16:12.513 --> 16:15.971
You care, because if Boyko finds out
that I screwed up this carjacking case,

16:16.017 --> 16:17.882
take a wild guess which training officer

16:17.935 --> 16:21.018
he's gonna drag into his office
and scream at for half an hour.

16:21.063 --> 16:22.143
All right, all right. All right.

16:22.190 --> 16:23.396
Calm down. What do you need?

16:24.859 --> 16:26.975
Okay, Luke brought in this kid,
Benjamin Kelly,

16:27.028 --> 16:28.643
and all of his personal effects
are in booking.

16:28.696 --> 16:30.277
See if you can find his cell phone.

16:30.323 --> 16:31.608
Jeez.

16:31.657 --> 16:35.115
Oh, and, um, Luke took the car,
so could you pick me up?

16:37.830 --> 16:39.741
Please?

16:41.125 --> 16:42.114
Ah.

16:42.168 --> 16:44.625
Yeah.

16:44.670 --> 16:46.626
(Noelle) This one just came in.

16:46.672 --> 16:49.664
It's an accident.
Contents need to be catalogued.

16:49.717 --> 16:51.332
Sure thing.

16:54.597 --> 16:56.087
Yes?

16:56.140 --> 16:57.516
Uh, we were just wondering,

16:57.558 --> 16:59.674
uh, if there was anything in particular
we were looking for,

16:59.727 --> 17:01.683
with regards to the carjackings.

17:03.272 --> 17:06.810
You know how some people say
that, uh, there's no stupid questions?

17:07.360 --> 17:08.475
They're wrong.

17:11.614 --> 17:14.947
Dov, this is just overflow
from the impound lot.

17:14.992 --> 17:17.153
Okay, we're painting a fence here.
We're rookies.

17:17.203 --> 17:19.159
This has nothing to do
with the carjackings.

17:20.790 --> 17:23.827
Uh, we've got some bills...

17:23.960 --> 17:25.291
paid.

17:25.336 --> 17:26.826
Um...

17:26.879 --> 17:28.460
Pen. Broken pen.

17:28.965 --> 17:30.830
Maps, folded.

17:31.634 --> 17:33.920
And a tin of, I don't know,
friggin' peppermint.

17:33.970 --> 17:36.928
- Hey. Hi.
- Hi. Join the fun.

17:36.973 --> 17:38.634
Yeah, we were actually
on the scene of this one.

17:38.683 --> 17:40.389
Oh, whoa.
Let me guess--uh, old guy.

17:40.434 --> 17:41.719
How'd you know?

17:41.769 --> 17:44.385
Nothing says golden years
like a tin of peppermints.

17:45.106 --> 17:46.471
(laughs)

17:48.025 --> 17:50.858
- Fatal?
- Uh, yes, for the cyclist that he hit.

17:50.903 --> 17:53.815
Yeah, we're looking for, uh,
any evidence of too many meds.

17:53.864 --> 17:56.651
If the driver was taking a lot of pills,
it might explain what happened.

17:56.701 --> 17:59.317
See, Chris is kind of worried about
the old guy. I think it's sweet.

17:59.370 --> 18:01.486
Well, knock yourselves out.

18:01.539 --> 18:03.325
Yeah, we'll take it from here.

18:04.417 --> 18:05.657
(pills rattle)

18:05.710 --> 18:08.497
- All right.
- Thanks.

18:08.546 --> 18:11.709
I'm telling you,
Gail totally wants to get with me.

18:11.757 --> 18:14.043
Now I'm not saying
I'm gonna ask her out, but--

18:14.093 --> 18:15.253
Please shut up.

18:17.221 --> 18:18.506
What's with you today?

18:19.140 --> 18:20.846
Who is she?

18:20.891 --> 18:23.974
Keisha Simmons. Number one
on Benny's speed dial.

18:24.020 --> 18:25.976
Oh, thanks for bringing her in.

18:26.022 --> 18:27.683
Yeah. Remember...

18:27.732 --> 18:29.939
she's under no obligation
to answer any questions,

18:29.984 --> 18:32.521
so... don't push your luck.

18:32.570 --> 18:35.107
Be nice. Ask the important
questions first. Got it?

18:35.156 --> 18:37.147
- Yeah, got it.
- (mouth full) all right.

18:39.118 --> 18:41.109
(door beeps)

18:42.622 --> 18:43.702
Hi.

18:43.748 --> 18:44.988
(door closes)

18:45.708 --> 18:46.914
What did Benny do now?

18:46.959 --> 18:49.871
ljust want to talk to him.
You a friend of his?

18:49.920 --> 18:51.956
Ex. Very ex.

18:52.006 --> 18:54.122
Never-want-to-see-
the-bastard-again ex.

18:54.175 --> 18:56.211
Hmm. 'Cause you're number one
on his speed dial.

18:56.260 --> 18:57.716
Yeah, and the last time he called,

18:57.762 --> 19:00.925
I told him I didn't want to talk to him--
not then, not ever.

19:02.767 --> 19:03.973
What do you want to talk to him about?

19:04.018 --> 19:05.883
He's helping us with an investigation.

19:05.936 --> 19:07.392
Helping the police?

19:09.065 --> 19:11.522
Doesn't sound like the Benny I know.

19:11.567 --> 19:14.730
The other cop said I was free to go
any time I wanna, and I wanna.

19:14.779 --> 19:17.191
Uh, okay, well, if you hear
from him, tell him to call me?

19:18.324 --> 19:19.564
Sure, but I'm not gonna
hear from him.

19:19.617 --> 19:21.198
Listen, does Benny
have a sick mother?

19:21.243 --> 19:22.278
Mm.

19:23.120 --> 19:24.496
His parents are dead.

19:25.122 --> 19:27.329
He used his mother's funeral excuse
on me twice.

19:27.375 --> 19:30.333
Okay, well, if you were trying to find him,
where would you look?

19:30.419 --> 19:31.955
I wouldn't look.

19:33.756 --> 19:35.792
(door buzzes, beeps)
Thanks.

19:39.762 --> 19:41.298
Hey, I was thinking that maybe
we should check out--

19:41.347 --> 19:43.087
Previous addresses?
I'm way ahead of you.

19:43.140 --> 19:44.471
Here's his latest.

19:45.476 --> 19:48.434
37 Seneca Drive--
Dabramo, initial's "M."

19:48.479 --> 19:50.435
- Any warrants?
- None in the system.

19:51.482 --> 19:52.471
Maybe it's a girlfriend.

19:52.525 --> 19:55.938
Yeah, maybe.
You know, if this guy was a witness

19:55.986 --> 19:57.021
to your carjacking murder,

19:57.071 --> 19:59.107
you'd better hope you find him
before Kraker's buddy does.

20:00.324 --> 20:01.780
Well, Benny didn't seem
too worried about that.

20:01.826 --> 20:04.067
Well, I should really go with you.

20:04.120 --> 20:06.111
No, no, no, listen.
I totally screwed this up.

20:06.163 --> 20:09.496
I need to fix it.
So just lend me the keys to your truck.

20:09.542 --> 20:10.827
I'm gonna go look at the address,

20:10.876 --> 20:13.208
and then you can blow the whistle on me
and ruin my entire career.

20:13.254 --> 20:14.994
I'm sorry.
You want to borrow my truck?

20:16.048 --> 20:18.209
Okay, we can just go talk to Boyko
right now. No problem.

20:23.639 --> 20:24.924
Brakes are touchy, all right?

20:24.974 --> 20:27.056
- Just careful.
- Okay.

20:31.355 --> 20:34.643
Hey, pal, I thought, uh,
Callaghan had your rookie today.

20:34.692 --> 20:35.807
Yeah, well, Callaghan's busy.

20:35.860 --> 20:36.895
Oh.

20:38.070 --> 20:39.685
What? I'm helping her out.

20:39.739 --> 20:40.854
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

20:42.408 --> 20:43.397
Find anything?

20:43.451 --> 20:46.488
Mm, gramps needs to pay
his Auto Club bill.

20:46.537 --> 20:49.950
He's got perfect penmanship,
but there's no pill receipts.

20:49.999 --> 20:52.365
Is there, uh, any numbers?
Anyone we can call?

20:52.710 --> 20:53.870
Nope.

20:54.211 --> 20:56.293
There's gotta be someone.

20:56.797 --> 20:58.003
Maybe if we knew
where he was going...

20:58.048 --> 20:59.128
(GPS beeps)

21:01.677 --> 21:04.168
- Wait. That's weird.
- What?

21:04.221 --> 21:08.965
Well, that's the cyclist's address
in The Beaches...

21:09.018 --> 21:12.681
and that's where we found him
dead on the side of the road.

21:14.356 --> 21:16.187
W-What?

21:18.944 --> 21:20.525
(Dov) Oh, this is--this is great.

21:20.571 --> 21:24.314
We're stuck here handling
the world's grossest evidence

21:24.366 --> 21:26.527
while everybody else
is out working actual cases.

21:26.577 --> 21:28.568
I know. It's disgusting.

21:29.330 --> 21:32.572
Absolutely nothing cool about this job.

21:35.252 --> 21:36.241
Whoa.

21:37.588 --> 21:38.577
Can I see that?

21:39.590 --> 21:40.579
What is it?

21:40.633 --> 21:44.171
Uh, it's a saber from "The Righteous War
of the Pontoon Pirates."

21:44.220 --> 21:45.300
Which is?

21:45.346 --> 21:48.554
Video game.
Man, | always wanted one of these.

21:48.599 --> 21:50.260
(exhales) Never got it.

21:52.353 --> 21:55.891
Now, okay, what is with you today?

21:55.940 --> 21:58.272
Leo's dad bought him a toy gun.

21:58.317 --> 21:59.557
So?

21:59.610 --> 22:01.942
I don't want Leo playing with guns.

22:03.072 --> 22:04.403
(chuckles, scoffs)

22:04.448 --> 22:07.030
What? Were your parents
letting you play with guns?

22:07.076 --> 22:10.489
No. My mom only bought us
educational toys from Sweden.

22:10.538 --> 22:13.951
We were on a strict diet of
peace, love and baby--Whoa!

22:15.960 --> 22:16.949
Blood.

22:18.838 --> 22:20.794
- No way.
- Yes way.

22:20.840 --> 22:22.205
That is so coffee.

22:22.258 --> 22:24.249
No, it's blood.
I'll bet you 20 bucks.

22:24.301 --> 22:26.383
(shakes hand)
We'll go ask Noelle.

22:27.304 --> 22:28.419
Not it.

22:28.472 --> 22:29.678
Oh, come on. She likes you.

22:29.723 --> 22:31.759
She's had it in for me since Day One.

22:31.809 --> 22:33.800
Okay, fine. I'll go ask her.
You, uh, bag it up.

22:33.853 --> 22:35.093
Okay, okay.

22:35.145 --> 22:37.272
All right. I'm going.

22:47.283 --> 22:48.989
- Hey.
- Oh.

22:49.159 --> 22:50.774
- It's not what it looks like.
- Sorry.

22:50.828 --> 22:53.160
They're hormones. Shut the door.

22:56.041 --> 22:57.542
(sighs)
(door creaks, closes)

22:58.794 --> 23:01.285
I'm really sorry.
I had no idea.

23:01.338 --> 23:03.795
lt's--lt's harder than it looks.

23:05.175 --> 23:06.790
I need the mirror to--

23:07.511 --> 23:08.842
to hit the right spot.

23:12.349 --> 23:13.964
(scoffs)

23:15.477 --> 23:17.217
This must look pretty desperate, huh?

23:18.856 --> 23:20.767
Fertility clinic, sperm donor...

23:22.902 --> 23:25.143
(sighs deeply)

23:25.195 --> 23:28.153
You know what I see
when I look at this thing?

23:30.034 --> 23:31.820
| see nine years...

23:33.787 --> 23:36.745
nine years with the same guy
who didn't want kids.

23:39.168 --> 23:41.454
Same guy who just had a baby
with his new girlfriend.

23:44.465 --> 23:45.454
Well, I don't know.

23:46.091 --> 23:48.833
| see someone who wants
something so much

23:49.929 --> 23:52.386
that she's willing to stick
a needle in her ass to get it.

23:55.601 --> 23:59.514
You know, it's not easy finding someone,
doing this job.

23:59.563 --> 24:01.269
I don't want to scare you, but it's true.

24:02.566 --> 24:05.854
Well, having a kid's
not gonna make it any easier.

24:05.903 --> 24:08.815
I don't want to scare you,
but that's true.

24:12.326 --> 24:13.907
Is this your first time?

24:15.454 --> 24:16.489
Yep.

24:17.247 --> 24:19.829
I gotta do 'em twice a day for two weeks,

24:19.875 --> 24:22.457
and it's, uh, kind of wigging me out.

24:23.337 --> 24:25.453
You know, like, stabbing yourself
with a needle--

24:25.506 --> 24:29.124
it's a little counterintuitive.

24:29.176 --> 24:31.542
(both laugh)

24:32.054 --> 24:33.339
You want me to do it?

24:46.777 --> 24:48.733
Thing is, uh,

24:50.239 --> 24:52.696
Boyko's gone in a few weeks,

24:52.741 --> 24:54.072
and I'm up for a promotion.

24:54.118 --> 24:55.608
SO if this--

24:57.204 --> 24:59.445
If this doesn't work out,
then I want those stripes.

25:00.124 --> 25:03.537
And if, uh, if anyone finds out,
I'll know it was you.

25:03.877 --> 25:04.866
- Ow!
- (chuckles)

25:07.297 --> 25:08.628
(laughs)

25:16.265 --> 25:17.596
I won't tell a soul.

25:27.443 --> 25:29.434
(cell phone rings)

25:31.113 --> 25:32.148
(ring)

25:32.364 --> 25:33.865
Uh... ooh...

25:34.408 --> 25:35.523
(ring--beep)

25:35.826 --> 25:38.363
Hey. What's happenin'?

25:38.412 --> 25:40.448
Sorry, I'm still trying
to track down this prosecutor,

25:40.497 --> 25:42.453
which is taking a lot longer
than I thought.

25:42.499 --> 25:45.241
Oh, oh, totally cool.
You know, you should take your time.

25:45.294 --> 25:48.161
How's our guy? Please tell me
you've talked him into giving up the bullet

25:48.213 --> 25:49.248
so I can get the hell out of here.

25:49.673 --> 25:50.662
Uh...

25:50.716 --> 25:52.001
Hang on.
I'm getting another call.

25:53.552 --> 25:55.292
It's the prosecutor.
I gotta go. I'll call you back.

25:55.345 --> 25:56.425
Okay. I...

26:00.517 --> 26:03.509
(siren wailing in distance)

26:11.195 --> 26:12.310
(knocks on door)

26:15.157 --> 26:16.192
Come on.

26:19.953 --> 26:21.454
(door creaks)

26:21.497 --> 26:22.657
Hello, Benjamin.

26:22.706 --> 26:24.082
(low voice)
How'd you find me?

26:24.124 --> 26:25.159
You're coming with me.

26:25.209 --> 26:26.324
I can't.

26:26.376 --> 26:27.832
- Okay, then I'll arrest you.
- What?

26:27.878 --> 26:28.913
Let's go!

26:28.962 --> 26:30.623
Okay, all right.
Just give me a minute.

26:30.672 --> 26:32.287
(woman) Benny,
who are you talkin' to?

26:32.341 --> 26:34.172
(normal voice) It's okay, Mama.
l-lt's for me.

26:37.221 --> 26:39.678
There better be a damn good
explanation for this.

26:39.723 --> 26:41.679
Officer, if he's giving you any trouble--

26:41.725 --> 26:44.683
Mama, this is Officer McNally,

26:44.728 --> 26:47.219
and I've been--
I've been helping her out.

26:51.151 --> 26:52.357
It's true.

26:52.402 --> 26:54.688
He's been helping me out.

26:54.738 --> 26:57.480
Well, then, come on inside.

26:59.159 --> 27:00.399
Don't just stand there!

27:00.452 --> 27:01.783
(laughs)

27:02.621 --> 27:03.861
Okay.

27:11.421 --> 27:14.709
Look at me.
Look at the state of this place.

27:15.884 --> 27:17.749
You gonna take
all day down there?

27:18.929 --> 27:19.918
Want a cup of coffee?

27:19.972 --> 27:23.180
Oh, no coffee, thank you.
Uh, we're actually in a hurry.

27:24.101 --> 27:25.181
You're Benny's mother?

27:25.227 --> 27:28.014
Foster mother. At least, I was.

27:28.730 --> 27:31.938
Too much of a smartass now
to listen to me anymore.

27:32.568 --> 27:33.557
Marie Dabramo.

27:33.610 --> 27:35.225
Andy.

27:35.279 --> 27:36.940
Doesn't stop you telling me what to do.

27:37.906 --> 27:39.942
I should have thrown him out years ago.

27:39.992 --> 27:42.734
(chuckles) Yeah. That why you
want me to visit you every day?

27:42.786 --> 27:44.242
Benny, you almost done down there?

27:44.288 --> 27:47.246
He's a good boy, most of the time.

27:47.291 --> 27:51.079
But I could've drowned
by the time you got here.

27:51.128 --> 27:54.040
I told you l was gonna be here,
and I am.

27:54.089 --> 27:56.421
Okay.

27:56.466 --> 27:58.422
That should hold for now.

27:58.468 --> 28:00.379
l'll fix it for real later, okay?

28:00.429 --> 28:02.340
- Later?
- Yeah.

28:02.389 --> 28:04.926
Look, you're not gonna leave me
with this mess.

28:04.975 --> 28:07.307
Mrs. Dabramo, I'm sorry.
Benny's assisting us

28:07.352 --> 28:09.729
with a really important investigation.
We've gotta go.

28:09.771 --> 28:12.513
Yeah. |--| mean I promise
I'll be back, okay?

28:12.566 --> 28:15.433
All right? Mwah. Thank you.

28:15.485 --> 28:18.067
You're not gonna assist anybody
dressed like that.

28:18.113 --> 28:19.319
No, we really don't have time.

28:19.364 --> 28:24.279
No, I've got a fresh shirt out here for you.
I know because I washed it.

28:26.997 --> 28:29.454
So where's the other guy--
